# DigitalOcean DNS Management for VividMAS Platform

This rule covers DNS configuration for the VividMAS AI automation platform using DigitalOcean DNS services.

## **Project Overview**

**VividMAS Platform Services:**
- **n8n** (Workflow Automation) - Port 5678
- **Open WebUI** (AI Chat Interface) - Port 3000  
- **Flowise** (No-code AI Builder) - Port 3001
- **Supabase** (Database + Auth) - Port 8000
- **Langfuse** (LLM Observability) - Port 3030
- **SearXNG** (Privacy Search) - Port 8080
- **Ollama** (Local LLMs) - Port 11434
- **WordPress** (CMS) - Port 8080 (separate compose)

## **DNS Configuration Setup**

### **Domain Registration vs DNS Management**
- **Domain Registration**: GoDaddy (or other registrar)
- **Nameservers**: Changed to DigitalOcean nameservers
- **DNS Management**: DigitalOcean controls all DNS records

### **Required Subdomain Structure**
```
n8n.yourdomain.com          → n8n (port 5678)
webui.yourdomain.com        → Open WebUI (port 3000)
flowise.yourdomain.com      → Flowise (port 3001)
supabase.yourdomain.com     → Supabase (port 8000)
langfuse.yourdomain.com     → Langfuse (port 3030)
search.yourdomain.com       → SearXNG (port 8080)
ollama.yourdomain.com       → Ollama (port 11434)
wordpress.yourdomain.com    → WordPress (port 8080)
```

## **Environment Configuration**

### **Required .env Variables**
```bash
# Domain Configuration
N8N_HOSTNAME=n8n.yourdomain.com
WEBUI_HOSTNAME=webui.yourdomain.com
FLOWISE_HOSTNAME=flowise.yourdomain.com
SUPABASE_HOSTNAME=supabase.yourdomain.com
LANGFUSE_HOSTNAME=langfuse.yourdomain.com
SEARXNG_HOSTNAME=search.yourdomain.com
OLLAMA_HOSTNAME=ollama.yourdomain.com
WORDPRESS_HOSTNAME=wordpress.yourdomain.com
WORDPRESS_DOMAIN=wordpress.yourdomain.com

# SSL Configuration
LETSENCRYPT_EMAIL=your-email@yourdomain.com

# Security
N8N_SECURE_COOKIE=false  # Set to true when using HTTPS
```

### **Docker Compose Configuration**
```yaml
# In docker-compose.yml, n8n service environment:
- WEBHOOK_URL=https://n8n.yourdomain.com

# WordPress requires separate compose file update:
# In wordpress-compose.yml:
environment:
  - WORDPRESS_CONFIG_EXTRA=define("DOMAIN_CURRENT_SITE", "wordpress.yourdomain.com");
```

### **Caddyfile Configuration**
```caddyfile
{
    email {$LETSENCRYPT_EMAIL}
}

# All services use this pattern:
{$SERVICE_HOSTNAME} {
    reverse_proxy localhost:PORT
}

# WordPress addition:
{$WORDPRESS_HOSTNAME} {
    reverse_proxy localhost:8080
}
```

## **doctl CLI Setup & Usage**

### **Authentication Setup**
```bash
# Install doctl (if not installed)
brew install doctl

# Initialize authentication
doctl auth init
# Enter your DigitalOcean API token when prompted

# Verify authentication
doctl auth list
```

### **Domain Management Commands**
```bash
# List domains
doctl compute domain list

# List existing DNS records
doctl compute domain records list yourdomain.com

# Create A record template
doctl compute domain records create yourdomain.com \
  --record-type A \
  --record-name SUBDOMAIN \
  --record-data SERVER_IP \
  --record-ttl 300
```

### **Automated DNS Record Creation Script**
```bash
#!/bin/bash
DOMAIN="yourdomain.com"
SERVER_IP="YOUR_SERVER_IP"

# Array of subdomains to create
SUBDOMAINS=("n8n" "webui" "flowise" "supabase" "langfuse" "search" "ollama" "wordpress")

for subdomain in "${SUBDOMAINS[@]}"; do
    echo "Creating A record for ${subdomain}.${DOMAIN}"
    doctl compute domain records create $DOMAIN \
        --record-type A \
        --record-name $subdomain \
        --record-data $SERVER_IP \
        --record-ttl 300
done

# Verify all records were created
echo "Verifying DNS records:"
doctl compute domain records list $DOMAIN
```

## **Server Configuration Process**

### **1. Update Environment Variables**
```bash
# On server: /home/vivid/vivid_mas/.env
ssh root@SERVER_IP "cd /home/vivid/vivid_mas && cp .env .env.backup-domain"

# Update hostnames to use new domain
sed -i 's/N8N_HOSTNAME=.*/N8N_HOSTNAME=n8n.yourdomain.com/' .env
sed -i 's/# LETSENCRYPT_EMAIL=.*/LETSENCRYPT_EMAIL=your-email@yourdomain.com/' .env
# ... repeat for all services
```

### **2. Update Docker Compose Configuration**
```bash
# Update n8n webhook URL
sed -i 's/WEBHOOK_URL=.*/WEBHOOK_URL=https:\/\/n8n.yourdomain.com/' docker-compose.yml

# Update WordPress domain
sed -i 's/WORDPRESS_DOMAIN:-localhost/WORDPRESS_DOMAIN:-wordpress.yourdomain.com/' wordpress-compose.yml
```

### **3. Update Caddyfile**
```bash
# Add WordPress configuration to Caddyfile
echo '' >> Caddyfile
echo '# WordPress' >> Caddyfile
echo '{$WORDPRESS_HOSTNAME} {' >> Caddyfile
echo '    reverse_proxy localhost:8080' >> Caddyfile
echo '}' >> Caddyfile
```

### **4. Restart Services**
```bash
# Restart main services
docker-compose restart caddy n8n

# Restart WordPress (separate compose)
docker-compose -f wordpress-compose.yml restart
```

## **Verification & Testing**

### **DNS Propagation Check**
```bash
# Check DNS propagation
dig n8n.yourdomain.com
nslookup n8n.yourdomain.com

# Test all subdomains
for sub in n8n webui flowise supabase langfuse search ollama wordpress; do
    echo "Testing ${sub}.yourdomain.com:"
    dig +short ${sub}.yourdomain.com
done
```

### **SSL Certificate Verification**
```bash
# Check SSL certificate status
curl -I https://n8n.yourdomain.com

# Monitor Caddy logs for certificate generation
docker logs caddy --follow
```

